\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid4786465 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 You were born in Barra?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Born in Barra in 1891. Not yesterday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 You came over to Vatersay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 In 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Can you describe the house you lived in when you first came to Vatersay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
Well, it was a - the - it was the old house that the shepherd has left. The shepherd left it - in - in - his family left the house and they took a fa
rm over in the village of Vatersay, and when we - emigrated over from we were - we were included in the raiders of course, this was the house we took - we occupied because it happened to be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10314060\charrsid2102334  }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 on a holding. And the shepherd's house happened to be on the holding and we were very welcomed through the shepherd's family to go to that house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 But the shepherd was no longer living there himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 No, no, he was down in - the family went over to the village of Vatersay, they - they themselves took a - a croft too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Can you describe the house to me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
The house dear was a - a stone built - rough built house. With a thatched roof, and - a - an open hearth, and - mostly logs were burnt because there's no peat on this island, it used to be - you know - th
e sea - what - logs that the sea used to - what do you call it, driftwood. Driftwood, that's it, that's correct, now driftwood. And - it was mostly what we were burning at the time. And - very crude wooden - wooden - you know, partitions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 How many partitions were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
There was two. A partition dividing the kitchen from the - the - the - living room from the bedroom place. There was two box beds, you know, and there was another see room called the - another room, was no window on the other wee 
room, and one bed there - too, and there's one bed there. And - and a window in the corner - a window - in the thatch, with hinges on that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10314060\charrsid2102334 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 ould be opened, closed at night time. Well there was a window - window in the kitchen too could be - you know. What 
else now dear? There was a seat outside - we used to put the buckets of water and - we'd draw the water from the well, then we'd leave the buckets outside. And - three legged pots you know, for the cooking. A girdle for the scones. What else had we now? I
 can't remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 A table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
Oh dear, yes dear, oh aye, we had a table and we had chairs, and - there was a bench, left by the - by the - by the - shepherd's family, two - a plank, yes, as a bench. Earthen floor, sweep it up and then sand, clean sand on it. Uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 When you did the washing did you do it in the burn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 No dear, in a tub, hot water, we used to boil it, by a big pot, boiled the water and do our washing and then - burn wasn't very near us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Would some people wash in the burn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Oh some did. Yes, some did. And had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10314060\charrsid2102334 fire}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334  by the burn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10314060\charrsid2102334 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
side. Oh yes. Especially blankets. That's where they used to wash the blankets. Have a fire on - on - at the burn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10314060\charrsid2102334 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
side, and - wash their blankets in the tubs there. Boil the water in the big pots and - poured the water into tubs and then tramped the blankets with their bare feet. Uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 In the box beds did two people share a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Oh yes, two sisters and two brothers, yes, yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 It was like a double was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Yes dear, it was a roof - with a top on, yes. Uh uh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Can you tell me your father, did he do anything for the children in the home when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 My father dear - was - I don't remember my father being a winter at home - sailing the seven seas, be
cause my father - my father was a very very very shy man, he - and gentle, refined in his ways, and he - the f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10314060\charrsid2102334 ishing - was his only allottery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 . And he with six children - packed his bag and go sailing, he's been all round the world my father, God have his m
ercy on his soul. But he used to be home for about six weeks in summertime, and working while at home for these six weeks as - a boatman. Really - going out to the - to the corn boats that used to be in Castlebay waiting for to be loaded with herring barr
els.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 That was the only time he was at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
Yes, in the summertime only. And - few - well when we came over here in 1910 - a few weeks - in the springtime, and then he was home once in autumn, and he started to pack and I'll tell you his words. 
Mother came here, it wasn't father at all, but she came here - thinking that she - he would - she would make him give the sea up, when he would take up - when she would - they would take the croft, a croft. She was so hurt you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10314060\charrsid2102334 know, I remember my mother si}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
tting inside the door, like this was the door open, crying and praying, used to have waves on this door. Well - she came over - over here, it was her real that he came on c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10314060\charrsid2102334 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 ndition that he would give up the sea. Thinking that he would make a life if he had a small croft, eight acres. Of - land, no plough, no horse, no nothing, but}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10314060\charrsid2102334  the spade. Well in the autu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10039129\charrsid2102334 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
 he said, this won't do, he said, and he packed his bag. This won't pay me, he said, I can't bring up my family he says understand. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 So he was away again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
Yes dear. And all the time - and he was away in the first world war and he was - what was it again - transport. And he was three miles off the Faulkland Islands, they weren't allowed during the first world war to go nearer land than tha
t, he was three miles - offside the Faulkland Islands and they used to coal - the battleships. And at the Jutland battle - didn't the Dreadnought and the Glasgow, two cruisers, British cruisers - came to them, alongside to them there and all holes at the 
side of the - the Dreadnought. Oh boys, boys, says my father, my}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10039129\charrsid2102334  father heard them talking the G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
aelic, boys, boys, he said, where are you from - out of reach? He says, Jutland battle. Well - he was - their - their boat was full of coal, you know, they were 
a coaling station - coming to Britian for the coal and going back - you see they had the three miles limit, you know, got the coal for - coal for the battle ship. Oh yes, yes. He was at the sailing, at the deep sea sailing right on - to - 1919. 1919. 'Til
 my two brothers were able to help, go to sea to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Then he stayed home did he after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
He - he did stay at home, he stayed at home dear when - my mother had died. He was at Albany, Western Australia, loading on the - he was at Albany, Western Australia - on the - Donegal - when the Donegal was away from - went on her}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10039129\charrsid2102334  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
maiden - maiden voyage and my father was on board, and he was loading grain, Albany Western Australia, 1912 when my mother died. Well then after my mother died and he came home, he had to carry on, we were too young to be left you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 And he carried on on the croft then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
Well dear he did, he did carried on the croft then. He made up his mind that he would carry on you know the croft as the other two - as the boys, John and Phil, God rest their soul - went out to sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Did they send money back then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 They were sending dear their half pay to my father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 They were good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 They were good, and - we too at the fishing in Lerwick and Yarmouth and 
- Glassing Island, the Isle of Mann, and - Peterhead, Aberdeen. We were bringing home a little money at the end of the season to help the home. Mm hm.
