\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Did she have a loom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 No dear, i
t - there wasn't a loom in every house at all, but there would be two looms in every village. Mm hm. At least two, in every village. Mm hm. And knitting, knitting stockings and knitting - oh knitting all the jers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8853191\charrsid2102334 ey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 s and knitting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8853191\charrsid2102334 bodices}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
 and shawls you know, the wool}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8853191\charrsid2102334 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 en things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Did your brothers learn to knit also?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 No, they did not. No. There was too much of the sea in their veins. Sea - seafaring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Did some boys knit, some men or was it a woman's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Oh women. Women. Women. They were m
ost - it was mostly the fishing for them. The fishing, the fishing, the fishing for them. And the sea, away for them going to sea. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 When you were a child did you have to go to bed at a certain time or did that not matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Yes. We had to go -
 to bed - wash your feet, scrub them or else I will take a clothful of sand and - get the mud - oh I used to cry - and have hags - hags on the feet. Mm hm. Going out after the mud you know and - huh, we had to wash our feet. Say our prayers, and go to bed
. But would we sleep, not us. Their children couldn't be what they are now. Too much - liberty, too much freedom, too much money.
