A lot of change, a lot of change, modern, to be modern. Mm. O gracious, gracious, gracious, it burns my heart dear when I - how modern they - they are today, but it's the parents that's smothering them that's the cause of it. Now dear - the fi
rst place on the first step that pare}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8853191\charrsid2102334 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
ts should do - is bring them properly up and teach them at their own fireside, don't leave it to school don't leave it to a pr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8853191\charrsid2102334 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
est or a minister, parents must do their duty, it's their duty - what they're promising - at the altar of God, with the blessed sacrament }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8853191\charrsid2102334 of matrimony. To fulfi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 l their duty as regards bringing up their children and - in the love and the fear of God, they should do it. Well that was in our days. But dear, dear, the change now. The change is terrible.
