o to the - fishing. Mm hm. Fishing, that was a great help, the fishing was - in full swing in Barra. But - that's when the first world war broke out, the markets - the - the markets went flop, such as Russia, Germany, and America, they used to buy the her
r
ing here, of course cured. There was - America large, and - the there was Hamburg, it was Hamburg again, I think it was - I can't remember everything - and then - the rest was going to the Baltic to Russia. Oh it was - used to be a very busy port, Castleb
a
y, in my young days. Three and four foreign boats loading - cured herring - for the Baltic, for Germany, for America. Mm hm. And that's - besides that there used to be - Norwegians, and - Norwegians - and all them with the Balkan Peninsular, you know, the
se countries. Is it called the Balkan Peninsular they call it? Norway, Sweden and Denmark, that's right, mm hm. That's right, yes, Scandinavia, yes.
