ever dear, never, I remember - a widow woman - coming to my mother - to ask my mother for a loan of two or three shillings. Well mother - thanked God always he was - she was able to give a shilling if a person was in need. Of course with intentions made t
hat they would soon give it back or if not she wouldn't bother. She must always - a shilling, two shillings, or - but - not - not above that. No, because - out of two pound a month dear with six of a family and herself - uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 The littlest children, before they could feed themselves, how were they fed, did they sit at the table in a high chair?
