Well to tell you the truth, I will just give you a picture of my - of our own home, my father and mother in my young days. Right up dear 'til the day that I married until the day he died. Never - never - 
never - do I recall - seeing my father coming home - with drink on, nor the smell of drink. Never - never he'd say to mother, when she would be busy - Annie, now take your time. There is no hurry. He would be home, you know, on leave but - but - no hurry 
A
nnie, just take your time. Don't take - don't hurry yourself, plenty of time, Annie, plenty of time. When he - and he was a great man for shooting, hunting. He used to go to - go shooting and hunting to the side of Barra, from Kentangval. When dusk come, 
oh my goodness, what has happened, what's keeping your father? Away she would go. Oh they - he - he - they really, really and truly - it was a blessed home.
