No, but I know what they used to do, the boys, the boys - get - iris - iris, and - pluck the iris and throw - roll up the - the iris like this and then put a sail on to make a boat and go down to the ponds the wee ponds for to sail - sail 
them. That was their way of life, mostly the boys, yes and I'll tell you another games the boys used to have - they'd get a ball - ball and a cannon, you know, what did you call that again - a stick with a - a - a round crook on it, like at - they used to
 
get the sticks in the woods in the wood in Braivic, and Northbay, and - their daddies used to bring them - cannon, cannon wood was - sticks with crooks on like that from the - from Skye and them places when they used to be at the winter fishing, herring f
ishing. And they would be so pleased that they had a cannon, it's a Cannon and gait they called it, a stick with a - a round crook on for - for to - the ball like this you know. You understand me, I can't -
