When your mother used to go back in the summer season to do the gutting of the herrings, how old were you children when she first started to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 My dear, she was - gutting - that was her first work you know,
 when she was able to help - the home - to go to the fishing, because of course Castlebay was a great fishing port as I've told you already, and it was - it was no distance at all to go - to walk from Kentangval to - to there, that's where their house was
 
and that's where we were staying too you know until the raiders tried - 1910, come over here. Mm hm. It was - the means of their livelihood, and the parents and the brothers - brothers would work in the - on the croft as well as the fishing. Crofter fishe
rmen. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 After she was married she used to go back and do it after the children were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 
Only in Castlebay, only in Barra only dear, only in Barra, during the summer season, and - the first of autumn, the autumn season, no more. She would have too - would be too busy at a home dear and father away at the sea. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 How old were the children when she started to go back for the season?
