hat was it, number Eleven Elsa Drive, Langside, Glasgow. One lady, Mrs Carmichael, she had - only one daughter and she was married to a doctor - Nottingham, I think that's outside London. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4786465 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 It's quite a way from London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10050444 KG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 Is it away from Lond
on? Ayes, yes. Well she was down for a time with them, but - she was such and independent lady she would like to be in her own villa, you know, how people - uh huh, in her own villa. Well she was ninety-six, when I was with her. Yes. Ninety-six, and when 
her husband died - oh - well her husband was dead - a year or so before I - I - went with her. In the dining room and sitting room she used to be - her - her glasses on, ninety-six mind you, and her magnifying glasses, the magnifying glass, and the books}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7808721\charrsid2102334  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4289636\charrsid2102334 li
ke this and - greeting it all. And she would tell me, oh Kate, she said, death duties in estates is so heavy on - on us. They had shares over there, in America. In the states. They had shares in Ceylon tea plantations. She said they had shares in - in Ale
xandria, Toushay or some place - houses, you know. \{BLANK\}
 And at that age she was in that state now, worrying about money and the death duties and - thought her awful foolish. Very foolish. What was she going to do with it, they were just in the coffin.
