ob here is quite all right with me. Well that's all right, Neil, I said, quite all right in a sense. But - should I be blessed with any - children I wouldn't like to bring them up here in Oban, I said, I would rather go home and get a croft, a small croft
.
 This one we have, well, an old man resigned, a relation of my husband, and he resigned the holding and my husband. So my husband came home, and he started to build - it was him that built all this house and put it up, just as you see it, and the gables, 
