hat's a Carrencrick gable, and the other gables are stone ones, stone and lime, but it was far too much for him to start a second one all on his own. I used to help him as regards the stone and - carrying the concrete and all that. But - however I stayed 
i
n Oban, I took a job, there was plenty of - of - you know daily work in Oban, and I carried on there and he came home and he built a - a shed - a wooden - small wooden cabin - there was the kitchen, the wkee room and - it would be quite all right for us i
